article.headline: New Hampshire 69, Stony Brook 56
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Tyrece Gibbs scored a career-high 22 points and had six rebounds to help New Hampshire beat Stony Brook 69-56 on Sunday. Jermaine Anderson added 14 points for the Wildcats (8-12, 4-3 America East). Ricky Lucas led the Seawolves (7-12, 2-5) with 18 points. Gibbs and Anderson combined for 26 of the Wildcats' 46 second-half points. New Hampshire used an 18-5 run to take a 17-point lead with 4:10 left.
